<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Whereas any obligation to serve requirements customers at the wholesale level is a contractual one, the traditional
obligation to serve at the retail level arises through utility monopoly franchise rights. The traditional retail
regulatory compact has ensured the utility's financial integrity by granting it an opportunity to recover prudently
incurred costs plus a fair rate of return, in exchange for regulation by the State regulatory authority and the duty
to provide safe, reliable, reasonably priced electric service on demand. Some states have recently considered whether
the traditional franchise duty to serve all customers within the boundaries of the designated franchise area ought
to evolve and whether this duty should be modified by the State.
