<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Pursuant to section 3021(a) of the Energy Policy Act of 1992 (Pub. L. 102&hyph;486), the Department of Energy (DOE)
shall, to the extent practicable, provide that not less than 10 percent of the total combined amounts obligated for
contracts and subcontracts pursuant to competitive procedures be expended with_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) small business concerns controlled by socially and economically disadvantaged individuals or by women; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) historically Black colleges and universities; or, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) colleges and universities having a student body in which more than 20 percent of the students are Hispanic Americans
or Native Americans. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) These three groups are collectively referred to in this section as ``Energy Policy Act target groups.'' 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) DOE shall vigorously pursue the objectives of section 3021 of the Energy Policy Act in the award of contracts and
subcontracts to the Energy Policy Act target groups. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) The DOE implementation of the requirements of section 3021 with regard to the award of Energy Policy Act procurements
consists of the following, ranked in descending order of preference: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Competitive awards to small disadvantaged businesses, including women-owned businesses, for Energy Policy
Act requirements under the Small Business Administration's section 8(a) program; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Competitive awards that provide an evaluation preference, in accordance with 926.7006, to offerors from the
Energy Policy Act target groups. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) The DOE implementation of section 3021 requirements with regard to the award of subcontracts under Energy Policy
Act procurements is discussed at 926.7006. 
